node.text: UO grad Jess Kokkeler, who knows a bit about lookouts, captured these shots of the Red Hill fire lookout in Wallowa-Whitman National Forest in eastern Oregon. The lookout offers sweeping views of the mountains and Wallowa Valley. Kokkeler (B.Arch., ’20, interior architecture) grew up building tree forts and more recently has helped game rangers in Zimbabwe build lookouts to spot poachers.
